{"title_page": "Anjana Singh", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2018}}\n{{notability|biographies|date=April 2018}}\n}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anjana Singh\n| image              =\n| alt                = Anjana Singh\n| caption            = Anjana Singh (left) with [[Pawan Singh]] (right) at IBFA Red Carpet in Singapore \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=1|1990|8|7}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = [[Actress]]\n| nationality        = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = {{ubl|''[[Love Aur Rajneeti]]''|''[[Nagraj]]''|''[[Sanki Daroga]]''}}\n| spouse             = \n}}\n\n'''Anjana Singh''' is an [[Indian people|Indian]] film actress. Singh was born on 7 August1990 in the Bahraich district of Uttar Pradesh into a Rajput family.Anjana Singh mainly works in [[Bhojpuri cinema|Bhojpuri]] films and television serials. She made her on-screen debut with  ''Ek Aur Faulad'' (2012) and her [[Bhojpuri cinema|Bhojpuri]] television debut was ''Bhag Na Bache Koi''.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!  Year  !! Film  !! Language\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Ek Aur Faulad]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Lahoo Ke Do Rang]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Lawarish]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Kaisan Piyawa Ke Charitar Ba]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Raja Ji I Love You''|| [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Saansar]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Truck Driver'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Vardiwala Gunda'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Dildar Sawariya'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Tuhi To Meri Jan Hai Radha'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Hathkadi'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Lahoo Pukarela'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Khoon Bhari Hamaar Maang'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Andhi Toofan'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Ek Nirahua Sarfira'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Baba Rangeela'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Pyar Mohabat Zindabad'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Dil Lagal Duppata Wali Se'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Dil Le Gai Odhganiya Wali'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Bihari Rikshawala'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Garda'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Ladaai'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Katta Tanal Dupatta Par'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Karela KLamal Dhartiu Ke Lal'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Kachche Dhaage'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Bahurani'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Lagi Tohse Lagan'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Ei Kaisan Pyar'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Hasina Maan Jayegi'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Gola Barood'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2015 || ''HamSe BadhKar Kaun'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Ballia Ke Dabangai'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Beta'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Mokama 0 KM'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Dil Hai Ki Manta Nahi'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Dabang Aashiq'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Khiladi'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Hero GamchaWala'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Doodh Ka Karz'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Love Aur Rajneeti'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2016  || ''Jouthi Tu Sethi Mu'' || [[Oriya language|Oriya]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Rani Dilbarjani'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Gundey Hai Hum'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Gundey'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Rangila'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Jigar'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Tere Jaise Yaar Kaha'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Trishool'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2017  || ''Sherdil Ghatak'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''[[Nagraj]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''[[Sanki Daroga]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Badrinath'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Khuddar'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Shiva Banal Don'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Munna Mawali'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Badla Hindustani Ka'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Maai Ke Biruwa'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2018  || ''Shahenshah'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2019  || ''Maine Unko Sajan Chun Liya'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2019  || ''Bitiya Chhati Mai Ke'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2019  || ''Saiyaan Ji Dagabaaz'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Ceremony\n! Category\n! Year\n! Film\n! Result\n! Reference\n|-\n|| [[International Bhojpuri Film Awards]] show [[London]]\n| Best Actress Viewers Choice\n| 2017\n|\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Best actress viewers choice award in london|url=https://www.channeleyenews.com/2017/08/01/anjana-singh-gets-best-actress-viewers-choice-award-in-london/|accessdate=12 April 2018|website=channeleyenews.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|| [[International Bhojpuri Film Awards]] show [[Malaysia]]\n| Best Actress\n| 2018\n| Jigar\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url= http://zeenews.india.com/bhojpuri/international-bhojpuri-film-awards-2018-check-out-the-list-of-winners-2126960.html|title=International Bhojpuri Film Awards 2018: Check out the list of winners|work=Zee News | date=23 July 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|7491231}}\n*{{Facebook|AnjanaSinghActress|Anjana Singh}}\n*Anjana Singh [https://independentnews.in/top-bhojpuri-actress-photos-2020/ Images]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Bhojpuri cinema actresses]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Anjana}}\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Lucknow]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Bhojpuri cinema]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n{{India-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2018}}\n{{notability|biographies|date=April 2018}}\n}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anjana Singh\n| image              =\n| alt                = Anjana Singh\n| caption            = Anjana Singh (left) with [[Pawan Singh]] (right) at IBFA Red Carpet in Singapore \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=1|1990|8|7}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = [[Actress]]\n| nationality        = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = {{ubl|''[[Love Aur Rajneeti]]''|''[[Nagraj]]''|''[[Sanki Daroga]]''}}\n| spouse             = \n}}\n\n'''Anjana Singh''' is an [[Indian people|Indian]] film actress. Singh was born on 7 August1990 in the Bahraich district of Uttar Pradesh into a Rajput family.Anjana Singh mainly works in [[Bhojpuri cinema|Bhojpuri]] films and television serials. She made her on-screen debut with  ''Ek Aur Faulad'' (2012) and her [[Bhojpuri cinema|Bhojpuri]] television debut was ''Bhag Na Bache Koi''.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!  Year  !! Film  !! Language\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Ek Aur Faulad]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Lahoo Ke Do Rang]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Lawarish]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Kaisan Piyawa Ke Charitar Ba]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Raja Ji I Love You''|| [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Saansar]]'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Truck Driver'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Vardiwala Gunda'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Dildar Sawariya'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''Tuhi To Meri Jan Hai Radha'' || [[Bhojpuri]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Hathkadi''