ists/dga-awards-2019-winners-list-full-1178563 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 3, 2019 |date=February 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Amy Sherman-Palladino <small>(for \"All Alone\")</small>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |[[American Society of Cinematographers|American Society of Cinematographers Awards]]\n| Outstanding Achievement in Cinematography for a Movie, Miniseries, or Pilot for Television\n| M. David Mullen <small>(for \"Pilot\")</small>\n| {{Nominated}}\n| align=\"center\" |<ref>{{cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |title=ASC Awards Nominations: \u2018Roma\u2019, \u2018A Star Is Born\u2019 & Others Make Cinematographers\u2019 Cut |url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/asc-awards-nominations-2019-cinematographers-alfonso-cuaron-roma-a-star-is-born-1202530561/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=January 7, 2019 |date=January 7, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[Cinema Audio Society Awards]]\n| Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing for a Television Series \u2013 One Hour\n| Mathew Price, Ron Bochar, Michael Miller, David Boulton & Steven Visscher <small>(for \"Vote for Kennedy, Vote for Kennedy\")</small>\n| {{Won}}\n| align=\"center\" |<ref>{{cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |title=CAS Awards: \u2018Black Panther\u2019, \u2018A Star Is Born\u2019 & \u2018Mrs. Maisel\u2019 Among Cinema Audio Society Nominees |url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/cas-awards-2019-nominations-black-panther-a-star-is-born-marvelous-mrs-maisel-cinema-audio-society-nominees-1202531016/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=January 8, 2019 |date=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Make-Up Artists and Hair Stylists Guild|Make-Up Artists and Hair Stylists Guild Awards]]\n| Television Series, Television Mini Series or Television New Media Series \u2013 Best Period and/or Character Make-up\n| Patricia Regan, Claus Lulla & Joseph A. Campayno\n| {{Won}}\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |titl