anuary 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[Costume Designers Guild Awards 2017|Costume Designers Guild Awards]]\n| Excellence in Period Television\n| [[Donna Zakowska]]\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nolfi |first1=Joey |title=I, Tonya, Get Out earn Costume Designers Guild nominations |url=http://ew.com/awards/2018/01/10/i-tonya-get-out-earn-costume-designers-guild-nominations/ |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=January 10, 2018 |accessdate=January 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[Location Managers Guild Awards#2018|Location Managers Guild Awards]]\n| Outstanding Locations in Period Television\n| Amanda Foley-Burbank & Jose Guerrero\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sandberg |first1=Bryn Elise |title='The Crown,' 'Dunkirk' Among Locations Managers Guild International Awards Nominees |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/crown-dunkirk-locations-managers-guild-international-awards-nominees-1087407 |accessdate=February 23, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=February 22, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[Peabody Award]]\n| Entertainment, children's and youth honoree\n|''The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel''\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.peabodyawards.com/award-profile/the-marvelous-mrs.-maisel |website=[[Peabody Awards]] |title=Peabody Awards: The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel|access-date=April 20, 2018 }}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[34th TCA Awards|Television Critics Association Awards]]\n| [[TCA Award for Individual Achievement in Comedy|Individual Achievement in Comedy]]\n| Rachel Brosnahan\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Moraes |first1=Lisa de |title=FX Russia Thriller \u2018The Americans\u2019 Takes TCA Trophies For Keri Russell, Best Drama And Program Of Year |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/tca-awards-the-americans-john-oliver-anthony-bourdain-good-place-rachel-brosnahan-friends-tv-critics-association-1202440215/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=August 5, 2018 |date=August 5, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"6\"| [[70th Primetime Emmy Awards|Primetime Emmy Awards]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Comedy Series|Outstanding Comedy Series]]\n| ''The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel''\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"6\"|<ref>{{cite news |last=Koblin |first=John |title=2018 Emmys: \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 and \u2018Marvelous Mrs. Maisel\u2019 Win Top Awards |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/17/arts/television/emmy-awards-live-updates.html |work=The New York Times |date=September 17, 2018 |accessdate=September 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"2018EmmyNoms\">{{cite web |last1=Hipes |first1=Patrick |title=Emmy Nominations: \u2018Game Of Thrones\u2019 Tops Noms, With Netflix & HBO Leading Way |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/2018-emmy-nominations-list-all-nominees-1202425072/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=July 12, 2018 |date=July 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Lead Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n| Rachel Brosnahan\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| [[Tony Shalhoub]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n| Alex Borstein\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Comedy Series|Outstanding Directing for a Comedy Series]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Amy Sherman-Palladino <small>(for \"Pilot\")</small>\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Comedy Series|Outstanding Writing for a Comedy Series]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"8\"| [[70th Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards|Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Guest Actress in a Co